name: r-spscomps
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.3.2.0" %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-spscomps
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/spsComps_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/spsComps/spsComps_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 57246223508d7b11e196ea53f28c65aedc117be3bce3679f6d53462ba589b1d9

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

# Suggests: testthat, shinyjqui, spsUtil (>= 0.1.2)
requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-assertthat
    - r-crayon
    - r-glue >=1.4.0
    - r-htmltools
    - r-magrittr
    - r-shiny >=1.5.0
    - r-shinyace
    - r-shinytoastr
    - r-stringr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-r6
    - r-assertthat
    - r-crayon
    - r-glue >=1.4.0
    - r-htmltools
    - r-magrittr
    - r-shiny >=1.5.0
    - r-shinyace
    - r-shinytoastr
    - r-stringr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('spsComps')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('spsComps')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/lz100/spsComps
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  summary: The systemPipeShiny (SPS) framework comes with many UI and server components. However, installing the whole framework is heavy and takes some time. If you would like to use UI and server components from SPS in your own Shiny apps, do not hesitate to try this package.

  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
